Find spatial expression modules using WGCNA

Matthieu Moreau1

30 novembre, 2020

Load libraries and QCFiltered dataset

# load libraries
library(Seurat)
library(WGCNA)
library(dendextend) 
library(dplyr) 
library(matrixStats) 
library(Matrix) 
library(RColorBrewer) 
library(ggdendro) 
library(tidyr) 
library(ggExtra)
library(patchwork)

# Set ggplot theme as classic 
theme_set(theme_classic())
# Load the full annotated dataset
Allcells.data <- readRDS("./Clustered.cells.RDS")

Extract LN and filter the dataset

ident.use <- unique(grep("LN", Allcells.data@ident, value = T))

Allcells.data <- SubsetData(Allcells.data, ident.use = ident.use, subset.raw = T,  do.clean = F)

colors <-  c("#ec756d", "#c773a7", "#7293c8", "#b79f0b", "#3ca73f","#31b6bd",
              "#ebcb2e", "#9ec22f", "#a9961b", "#cc3a1b", "#cc8778" , "#d14c8d", "#4cabdc", "#5ab793", "#e7823a","#e6bb9b", "#046c9a", "#4784a2" , "#4990c9")
DimPlot(Allcells.data,
        reduction.use = "spring", 
        dim.1 = 1,
        dim.2 = 2,
        do.label=T,
        label.size = 2,
        no.legend = T,
        cols.use = colors)

# Filter the gene expression matrix
num.cells <- Matrix::rowSums(Allcells.data@data > 0)
total.cells <- nrow(Allcells.data@meta.data)
genes.use <- names(x = num.cells[which(num.cells >= 90 & num.cells < 0.60*total.cells)])
Allcells.data@raw.data <- Allcells.data@raw.data[genes.use, ]
Allcells.data@data <- Allcells.data@data[genes.use, ]

# Normalize counts matrix
Allcells.data <- NormalizeData(object = Allcells.data,
                         normalization.method = "LogNormalize", 
                         scale.factor = round(median(Allcells.data@meta.data$nUMI)),
                         display.progress = F)

# Take the 1000 genes with the highest dispersion
Allcells.data <- FindVariableGenes(object = Allcells.data,
                                   selection.method = "dispersion",
                                   do.plot = F)

Run WGCNA

PSB.data <- data.frame(as.matrix(Allcells.data@data[Allcells.data@var.genes,]))
datExpr <- as.data.frame(t(PSB.data))

Choose a soft threshold power and compute network adjacency

enableWGCNAThreads(nThreads = 2)
## Allowing parallel execution with up to 2 working processes.
powers <- seq(from =1, to=30, by=1) #choosing a set of soft-thresholding powers

sft <- pickSoftThreshold(datExpr,
                        powerVector=powers,
                        verbose =0,
                        networkType="signed")

p1 <- ggplot(sft$fitIndices, aes(x = Power, y = -sign(slope)*SFT.R.sq)) +
      geom_text(aes(label = Power)) +
      geom_hline(yintercept = 0.7) + 
      ggtitle("Scale independence") +
      xlab("Soft Threshold (power)") + ylab("Scale Free Topology Model Fit, signed R^2")
      
  
p2 <- ggplot(sft$fitIndices, aes(x = Power, y = mean.k.)) +
      geom_text(aes(label = Power)) + 
      ggtitle("Mean Connectivity") +
      xlab("Soft Threshold (power)") + ylab("Mean Connectivity")


p1 + p2

# Pick the lowest power for which the scale free topology index reaches 0.7
softPower <- sft$fitIndices %>%
               filter(SFT.R.sq > 0.7) %>%
               pull(Power) %>%
               min()
adjacency <- adjacency(datExpr,
                      power = softPower,
                      corFnc = "cor",
                      corOptions =  list(use = 'p', method = 'spearman'),
                      type = "signed") #specify network type

Find modules

TOM <- TOMsimilarity(adjacency,  TOMType="signed")
## ..connectivity..
## ..matrix multiplication (system BLAS)..
## ..normalization..
## ..done.
dissTOM <- 1-TOM
# Clustered gene tree
geneTree <- hclust(as.dist(dissTOM), 
                     method = "average")

plot(geneTree,
     xlab="", sub="",
     main= "Gene Clustering on TOM-based dissimilarity", labels= FALSE, hang=0.04)

# Define the modules by cutting the tree
dynamicMods <- cutreeDynamic(dendro= geneTree,
                            distM= dissTOM,
                            cutHeight=0.99,
                            deepSplit=3,
                            pamRespectsDendro= FALSE,
                            minClusterSize = 10)
##  ..done.

Calculate modules eigengenes

# Calculates module eigengenes 
dynamicColors  <-  labels2colors(dynamicMods)

MEList <- moduleEigengenes(datExpr,
                           colors= dynamicColors,
                           softPower = softPower)

MEs <- MEList$eigengenes

Cluster modules according to their eigengene values

First clustering

MEDiss <- 1-cor(MEs, use = 'pairwise.complete.obs')

METree <- hclust(as.dist(MEDiss), 
                     method = "average")


#plots tree showing how the eigengenes cluster together
plot(METree, main= "Clustering of module eigengenes", xlab= "", sub= "")

Merge modules which are to closely related

# Set a threhold for merging modules. 
MEDissThres <- 0.2
merge <- mergeCloseModules(datExpr,
                          dynamicColors,
                          cutHeight= MEDissThres,
                          verbose =3)
##  mergeCloseModules: Merging modules whose distance is less than 0.2
##    multiSetMEs: Calculating module MEs.
##      Working on set 1 ...
##      moduleEigengenes: Calculating 6 module eigengenes in given set.
##    Calculating new MEs...
##    multiSetMEs: Calculating module MEs.
##      Working on set 1 ...
##      moduleEigengenes: Calculating 6 module eigengenes in given set.
mergedColors <- merge$colors

mergedMEs <- merge$newMEs

moduleColors <- mergedColors
colorOrder <- c("grey", standardColors(50))
moduleLabels <- match(moduleColors, colorOrder)-1
merged.MEDiss <- 1-cor(mergedMEs, use = 'pairwise.complete.obs')

merged.METree <- hclust(as.dist(merged.MEDiss), 
                     method = "average")


#plots tree showing how the eigengenes cluster together
plot(merged.METree, main= "Clustering of module eigengenes", xlab= "", sub= "")

Explore module activity across cells

Genes <- colnames(datExpr)
Modules <- moduleColors
GeneModules <- data.frame(Genes, Modules)
GeneModules <- plyr::arrange(GeneModules,Modules)
rownames(GeneModules) <- GeneModules$Genes

Allcells.data@meta.data <- cbind(Allcells.data@meta.data, mergedMEs)

write.table(GeneModules,"./WGCNA_GeneModules.csv", sep = ";", quote = F)
# Plot modules' eigengene values on spring embedding  
FeaturePlot(object = Allcells.data,
            features.plot = grep("ME", colnames(Allcells.data@meta.data), value = T),
            cols.use = rev(RColorBrewer::brewer.pal(n = 11, name = "Spectral")),
            reduction.use = "spring",
            no.legend = T)
